# Frontend TS + React conventions

- Follow existing patterns in nearby files before introducing new abstractions.
- Use named declaration exports; avoid default exports.
- For new React components, prefer function declarations over arrow component definitions.
- Name callback props/handlers with an `on` prefix.
- Keep naming consistent with Grafana style guides (`PascalCase` types/components, `camelCase` variables/functions).
- Add explicit return types for new functions.
- Keep files focused; split large components into smaller pieces.
- Put tests next to the implementation (`*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx`).

